Akron Mayor Don Plusquellic expresses his support for the tax cut framework agreement reached by President Obama and Republican congressional leaders. He believes that compromise is essential in addressing complex issues and that it was the right decision to work towards a solution, particularly in extending unemployment benefits and moving the country forward. He hopes that this agreement will lead to ongoing dialogue and actions from Washington to address the nation's problems, and emphasizes the responsibility of Republican legislators to meet the President halfway in future negotiations.